\C[25]\fiIve tried to make the enemies more challenging in this dungeon, but as a result its possible the difficulty will be frustrating and require you to go back and grind enemies to be able to fight in this dungeon, which I want to avoid if at all possible. For that reason, youll now have two difficulty downs in your inventory, which when used will increase your power and defense by five. I hope youll try fighting the enemies without using them first, but if you are struggling then these will help without requiring you to spend time fighting old enemies over and over. Also, if you find you are too strong and want more of a challenge, you have two difficulty ups as well, which will lower your power and defense by five. Each time you adjust the difficulty, youll get the opposite item, so if you use both difficulty ups, youll have four difficulty downs, so you can always undo the changes if youd like.
